comment.author: 77345821@N06
comment._content: This is not a Curtiss JN Canuck. It is a Standard J.I. There is no stagger to the wing struts, wings are not equal span, and no radiator. The engine is an inline six, probably a Hall-Scott, instead of the OX-5 or Hispano-Suiza Vee-eight engines of the Jenny.
